<p>For expats seeking outdoor activities beyond beaches and towns, the Apennine Mountains south and east of Rome offer hiking, nature exploration, and cooler mountain air during hot months. The Parco Nazionale d'Abruzzo, Lazio e Molise represents one of Italy's largest national parks, accessible as a full-day trip from Rome. The park offers hiking trails ranging from leisurely nature walks to challenging mountain climbs, with opportunities to observe Italian wildlife including Apennine wolves, red deer, and golden eagles in their natural habitats.</p>

